  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nFour of eight studies (including two replicated, randomized, controlled studies) in Argentina, Australia, Belgium, Israel, New Zealand, Spain, West Africa and the USA found that excluding livestock using wire fences increased  biomass , species richness, density and cover of understory plants. The other four studies\u00a0found mixed effects or no effect of livestock exclusion on understory plants.\nThree of four studies (including one replicated, randomized, controlled study) in Mexico, Kenya, Israel and Panama found that excluding livestock using wire fences increased the size and density of regenerating trees and the number of regenerating trees. One study\u00a0found livestock exclusion decreased tree density but not tree size."
}

